Anderson was beaten by now four time champion Novak Djokovic in the men's final on Sunday. JOHANNESBURG - The Sports Ministry has congratulated South African tennis player Kevin Anderson for his strong performance at this year's Wimbledon tournament. Anderson was beaten by now four-time champion Novak Djokovic in the men's final on Sunday. It took the South African-born athlete 21 hours of playing to reach the final. The result means that Anderson's world ranking will now move to fifth place. The Sports Ministry's Vuyo Mhaga: "The minister is proud of what Anderson has done. He has been such a great ambassador for the country and such an inspiration for our youth. Many young South Africans will now see tennis as a sport they can play. So we're quite proud of what he's done for our country."